+\paragraph{Project conclusion 3: checkpoint selection must not be ``take the latest''.}
+KnotPlot checkpoint quality is not assumed to improve monotonically.  The
+project therefore uses signed fractional length gain, per-component flatness,
+and a finite-thickness proxy
+\begin{align}
+    D_{\rm proxy}
+    &=
+    \min\!\left(2R_{\min},d_{\rm self}^{\rm nonlocal},d_{\rm inter}\right),
+    \\
+    \mathcal R_{\rm proxy}
+    &=
+    \frac{L}{D_{\rm proxy}},
+    \label{eq:genesis_knotplot_seed_proxy}
+\end{align}
+rather than raw length alone.  A signed plateau requires nonnegative but small
+improvements over successive checkpoints; a length regression is never called
+a plateau.  If no plateau is found within the preregistered scan range, the
+pipeline may retain a best-so-far seed only with an explicit
+\texttt{best-so-far-no-plateau} warning.
